<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>dfcsoftware Linux Home Administration - fosstodon</title><link href="https://dfcsoftware.github.io/" rel="alternate"></link><link href="https://dfcsoftware.github.io/feeds/fosstodon.atom.xml" rel="self"></link><id>https://dfcsoftware.github.io/</id><updated>2023-08-23T22:40:22+00:00</updated><entry><title>Alerts</title><link href="https://dfcsoftware.github.io/alerts.html" rel="alternate"></link><published>2023-08-23T22:40:22+00:00</published><updated>2023-08-23T22:40:22+00:00</updated><author><name>Don Cohoon</name></author><id>tag:dfcsoftware.github.io,2023-08-23:/alerts.html</id><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Finally got my alerts working, so when a host goes haywire I get an alert on the Phone and Cloud, with E-Mail as backup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Package is here:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linux-in-the-house.pages.dev/2023/august#download" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;linux-in-the-house.pages.dev/2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;023/august#download&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fosstodon.org/tags/linux" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;linux&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fosstodon.org/tags/alert" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;alert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fosstodon.org/tags/opensource" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;opensource&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="fosstodon"></category></entry><entry><title>QEMU Virtual Machine</title><link href="https://dfcsoftware.github.io/qemu-virtual-machine.html" rel="alternate"></link><published>2023-06-11T23:42:12+00:00</published><updated>2023-06-11T23:42:12+00:00</updated><author><name>Don Cohoon</name></author><id>tag:dfcsoftware.github.io,2023-06-11:/qemu-virtual-machine.html</id><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Virtual machines using &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fosstodon.org/tags/qemu" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;qemu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  is breezy/easy with &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fosstodon.org/tags/Cockpit" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;Cockpit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  on &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fosstodon.org/tags/AlmaLinux" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;AlmaLinux&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So glad I blasted an old machine to start my new resiliency strategy without proprietary VirtualBox or VMWare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check out some notes here:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ôªøhttps://linux-in-the-house.pages.dev/2023/june&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fosstodon.org/tags/linux" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;linux&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fosstodon.org/tags/opensource" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;opensource&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fosstodon.org/tags/vm" rel="tag"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;vm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><category term="fosstodon"></category></entry><entry><title>Long Ethernet</title><link href="https://dfcsoftware.github.io/long-ethernet.html" rel="alternate"></link><published>2023-05-19T22:41:39+00:00</published><updated>2023-05-19T22:41:39+00:00</updated><author><name>Don Cohoon</name></author><id>tag:dfcsoftware.github.io,2023-05-19:/long-ethernet.html</id><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Anyone ever extend an Ethernet connection over 1000 feet (350 meters)? Did you use coax?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I need to wire up another building with my existing router. No line of sight, and probably under ground (sand). &lt;/p&gt;
